The paper deals with the problem of aerial vehicle recognition using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of text-guided classification also involves natural language processing (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the training and testing of the model, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the model to aerial vehicles also involves robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of synthetic data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
